		<h1> Epiphanies sometimes hurt people</h1>
		<small> 11-05-2026 </small>

		<p>sorry folks this ones gonna be a bit ranty</p>
		<p> I think many of my epiphanies happen after a gestation period where you know something isn't right and then the solution becomes so clear</p>

		<p> Maybe that clarity is another delusion but! theres no harm in trying right?</p>

		<h2>I know I can't go on like this.</h2>
		<p> Instant Communication. Nothing on this earth has caused me as much stress as consistently as instant communication.</p>
		<p>I am not talking strictly digital either. Even conversationally I have caused problems but for the sake of scope lets stick to digital.</p>
		<p>Instant communication fails logic consistently. It removes friction which lets the impulsive mind act before premeditation can even take place.</p>
		<p>If you were not there or you couldn't tell already there was an incident.</p>
		<p>I let my emotions fester and they all came out all at once.</p>
		<p>They werent nice emotions either. They came from a place of hatred and frustration.</p>
		<p>It's so much easier to pace myself in person because I can see the other person.</p>
		<p>I can see that I am hurting them and I can know that I should stop.</p>
		<p>Conversation has invisible cues that just are not captured in text based formats.</p>

		<h2>Friends, Enemies, Those Who Lie Between and Those Who Lie Beyond.</h2>
		<p>There are a select few people whos friendlists are a tight ship. Only containing people they need to contact.</p>
		<p>If you are like me however, your friendlist has enough entries to pack a theatre and only a select few you enjoy talking to.</p>
		<p>It is a very binary way of looking at human relationships.</p>
		<p>There is friend and non-friend and no inbetween.</p>
		<p>There isn't a relationships tab in discord that shows you mutuals, people you've shared the most conversations with, people you've had the most fights with, people who you love and hate and are ambivilant towards.</p>
		<p>There are friends and non friends. And it is impolite not to accept someones friend request if they send one.</p>
		<p>And it is rude to unfriend someone.</p>
		<p>No more of that. I fucking hate that. I hate it. I hate it. I hate it.</p>

		<h2>The Friend Problem.</h2>
		<p>I don't think I have friends.</p>
		<p>Not to say that the people who I previously thought were my friends were cruel to me or anything.</p>
		<p>It is just that I'm scared.</p>
		<p>People are not allowed to get to know me.</p>
		<p>Within your first 3 interactions with me you either decide that being around me is fun or is not and that is as deep as I will allow our relationship to be.</p>
		<p>If you don't know who I am then I could be anyone.</p>
